However, he did praise the Obama administration for recently taking the Iranian dissident group Mujahedeen-e-Khalq, or MEK, off the U.S. terrorist watch list.

The group is a major anti-Ahmadinejad force that was allied with Saddam Hussein in the 1980s.

A coalition of Iranian-American groups organized the protest against Ahmadinejad - one of the largest gatherings staged against the Iranian leader in recent years during the General Assembly.

