Speakers included high-profile U.S. politicians including two former U.S. ambassadors to the U.N., Democratic U.S. Rep. Carolyn Maloney and former Rep. Patrick Kennedy.

Alireza Miryusefi, a spokesman for Iran's U.N. Mission, in a text message attributed the aggression of the protesters toward Mehmanparast to the MEK.

The 'MEK is going to be delisted and you can expect such a aggressive behavior of a terrorist sect. It would be another wrong step by U.S. administration. The responsibility of protecting all diplomats is on behalf of government of USA.'

